@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Ixim" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Ixim runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, simply click on any bar, either fixed or moveable. A
'fixed' bar, indicated by a 'pressed down' shape, cannot move. If
you click on a fixed bar, another -moveable- bar will either
randomly appear or disappear.

  Clicking on a 'moveable' bar, shown as a 'normal' bar, will make
it disappear and reappear at another location... or return to its
current location...

  A 'symmetry percentage', shown at the right of the game board,
indicates the percentage of bars that are symmetrically placed.

  Complete the game using the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

  You can restart the game by clicking on the 'New Game' button.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's closebutton
or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

